              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once we arrived in Cusco, we checked into our hotel and quickly made arrangements for the next day to get to Ollantaytambo, the town where our train to Machu Picchu would depart from. The same driver who picked us up from the train station agreed to make the drive, and offered to take us to some of the major stops in the Sacred Valley on our way. It was a great price, and since our hotel had arranged for him to pick us up originally, we felt like we were in good hands."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The next day, our driver picked us up after lunch. We drove out of Cusco and headed to our first stop on our tour of the Sacred Valley - Chinchero. Chinchero is a small town that holds some ancient ruins, a beautiful textile market, and an old colonial church. To enter the town, you must purchase a ticket. You can buy a ticket just for Chinchero, or you can be admitted with a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://theonlyperuguide.com/peru-guide/cusco/tourist-ticket/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Cusco Tourist Ticket"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", a much better deal. We had to look around quickly so that we could make it to the remaining stops on our tour before our train departed from Ollantaytambo that evening."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The official market is only open on Sundays, but we were able to see some of the textiles along the cobblestone streets, and we also got to see a demonstration of how the textiles are made. We picked up a couple of beautiful table runners (one for a gift and one for ourselves) from the woman who gave us the demonstration. Just note that if you watch the demonstration, there will be some pressure to make a purchase."
          }
        ]
