                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/BIRU-WP-20150806T151647GMT-0500.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Our next quick stop along our route to Ollantaytambo was the Maras Salt Mines, which were perhaps the most interesting of all of our stops that day. From our first peek of the mines from the road high above them, we were fascinated by how large and unique the hundreds of salt pools were. A single stream of salty water flows through each pool and leaves salt behind as it evaporates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
